      • determineLoadData

        com.kuka.geometry.LoadData determineLoadData(com.kuka.station.StationRobot stationRobot,
                                             ILoadDataDeterminationStepListener listener,
                                             double existingMass,
                                             com.kuka.math.geometry.Transformation existingCenterOfMass,
                                             com.kuka.math.physics.Inertia inertia,
                                             boolean useExistingMass,
                                             boolean useExistingCenterOfMass,
                                             boolean useInertia,
                                             com.kuka.device.common.JointEnum[] jointsToUse,
                                             JointRestrictionInfo[] axisRestrictions,
                                             String algorithmSpecificData)
                                      throws LoadDataDeterminationException
        determines the load data of a tool. A mass and center of mass can be specified to increase the accuracy of the other load data values.
        Parameters:
        stationRobot - The station robot.
        listener - The listener.
        existingMass - mass of the tool (can be 0 if not known).
        existingCenterOfMass - center of mass to use (can be null if not known).
        inertia - inertia to use (can be null if not known).
        useExistingMass - true if the specified mass should be used.
        useExistingCenterOfMass - true if the specified center of mass should be used.
        useInertia - true if the specified inertia should be used.
        jointsToUse - the joints that the algorithm can use for the load data determination.
        axisRestrictions - The joint restriction info.
        algorithmSpecificData - Plain text for algorithm specific data.
        Returns:
        the calculated load data object.
        Throws:
        LoadDataDeterminationException - an exception if occurred.

      • getCurrentMotionContainer

        com.kuka.motion.IMotionContainer getCurrentMotionContainer()
        Gets the motion container of the current motion of the load data determination. Can be null if no motion is in progress! The motion container is needed to cancel the motion when the load data determination process should be stopped.
        Returns:
        gets to current motion container.
